" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Urea as an ineffective osmole",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 414px; height: 309px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Effect of adding a permeable solute such as urea to the fluid on one side of a membrane that is permeable to water. In this setting, equilibrium is reached by urea equilibration across the membrane rather than water movement into the urea compartment. Consequently, no osmotic pressure is generated (estimated from the height of the column of water above the urea compartment).",
